obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (105886)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 15th day of March, 2026, vide notifn. No. S.O. 1243 (E), dated 10th day of March, 2026, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105886&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Coastal Shipping Act, 2025.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided; the provisions of this Act shall apply to---`
  line
  line `(a) every vessel, other than an Indian vessel, engaged in coasting trade, irrespective of the place of residence or domicile of the owner;`
  line
  line `(b) every chartered vessel referred to in Chapter IV; and`
  line
  line `(c) coastal waters of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on 1such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (105887)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105887&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "coasting trade" means carriage of goods or passengers by sea from any port or place in India to any other port or place in India, or performing any service within coastal waters but shall not include fishing of any kind.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this clause, "service" includes exploration, exploitation, research, and any other commercial activity in the coastal waters other than carriage of goods or passengers by sea;`
  line
  line `(b) "coastal waters" means any part of the territorial waters of India, along with any part of the adjoining maritime zones of India within the meaning of the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and Other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976), for undertaking coasting trade:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, specify any port or place including inland waters of India, as part of the coastal waters for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "committee" means the committee constituted under sub-section (3) of section 8 for preparing the National Coastal and Inland Shipping Strategic Plan;`
  line
  line `(d) "Director-General" means the Director-General appointed under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line
  line `(e) "Indian vessel" means any vessel registered in India under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line
  line `(f) "licence" means the licence issued by the Director-General under section 4 or section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) "licensee" includes the owner or master or charterer or operator or any person operating the vessel under a licence granted to such vessel by the Director-General;`
  line
  line `(h) "National Database of Coastal Shipping" means the database maintained by the Director-General under section 9;`
  line
  line `(i) "notification" means a notification published in the Gazette of India or the Official Gazette of a State, as the case may be, and the expression "notify" with its grammatical variation and cognate expressions, shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "principal officer" means the principal officer of the Mercantile Marine Department referred to in the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line
  line `(l) "proper officer" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (34) of section 2 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(m) "Strategic Plan" means the National Coastal and Inland Shipping Strategic Plan published under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(n) "vessel" includes every description of water craft, used or capable of being used in the marine environment, whether self-propelled or not, such as ship, boat, sailing vessel, fishing vessel, submersible, semi-submersible, hydrofoils, non-displacement crafts, amphibious crafts, wing-in-ground crafts, pleasure crafts, barges, lighters, mobile offshore drilling units and mobile offshore units.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (105888)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition on coasting trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105888&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No vessel, other than an Indian vessel, shall engage in coasting trade in the coastal waters, except under a licence granted by the Director-General under section 4:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director-General may, by order in writing, permit a vessel registered under the Inland Vessels Act, 2021 (24 of 2021), to engage in coasting trade to such extent and subject to such conditions, as may be specified in that order.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever engages any person to undertake coasting trade shall ensure that such person does not violate the provisions of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (105889)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Licence for coasting trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105889&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for the grant of a licence for coasting trade shall be made to the Director-General in such form, manner and on payment of such fee, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Before issuing a licence under this section, the Director-General shall take into consideration the following factors, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) whether the applicant has previously held a licence that was cancelled;`
  line
  line `(b) whether the applicant has engaged in violation of any of the provisions of this Act prior to or during the period of pendency of his application;`
  line
  line `(c) citizenship of the crew;`
  line
  line `(d) build requirements of the vessel;`
  line
  line `(e) availability of vessels on the route;`
  line
  line `(f) licences granted to vessels for the same route;`
  line
  line `(g) safety, national and maritime security concerns;`
  line
  line `(h) equipment on board the vessel including communication equipment;`
  line
  line `(i) the Strategic Plan under section 8;`
  line
  line `(j) cost efficiency of transport;`
  line
  line `(k) validity of the certificates of vessel and crew;`
  line
  line `(l) validity of the certificate of insurance of the vessel; and`
  line
  line `(m) any other requirements as the Director-General may consider necessary in furtherance of the objectives of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) A licence granted under this section shall be in such form, for such period and shall be subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director-General may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, specify such other conditions as may be necessary for grant of the licence.`
  line
  line `(4) The class or category of licence to be granted under this section shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (105890)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Suspension, revocation or modification of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105890&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director-General may, if the circumstances of the case so require to meet the objectives of this Act, by order in writing and for reasons to be recorded therein, suspend, revoke or modify a licence granted under section 4, if the licensee, or any person engaged by him---`
  line
  line `(a) violates any condition of the licence; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to comply with any requirement under any law for the time being in force applicable to the vessel; or`
  line
  line `(c) fails to comply with a direction issued under section 35; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to pay any fine or serve any sentence imposed under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the suspension, revocation or modification of licence under this clause shall not absolve the licensee from his obligation for payment of any fine or penalty, or undergoing any punishment, imposed on him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No licence granted under section 4 shall be suspended, revoked or modified under sub-section (1), unless the licensee has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) A licensee, who intends to modify the particulars of the licence granted to him under section 4, may make an application to the Director-General in that behalf in such form and manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the licence granted under section 4 ceases to be valid due to expiry of its period or revocation, the licensee shall---`
  line
  line `(a) return it or cause it to be returned to the Director-General; and`
  line
  line `(b) cease to engage in coasting trade,`
  line
  line `within such period as may be specified by the Director-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (105891)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Reporting requirements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105891&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every vessel, including Indian vessels engaged in coasting trade, shall report to the Director-General the following information in such form and manner as may be prescribed, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the port or ports which it will visit in the course of its voyage;`
  line
  line `(b) goods or passengers carried by such vessel and the ports or places where such goods or passengers will be dropped off;`
  line
  line `(c) any offshore area in which it may operate or navigate for the purposes of its voyage; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other information as the Director-General may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (105892)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Licence to be produced for port clearance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105892&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No proper officer shall grant clearance to a vessel, other than an Indian vessel, engaging in coasting trade to enter or depart from a port, unless the licensee or agent of such vessel produces the licence granted under section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any vessel fails to comply with the requirements of this Act, the Director-General or the principal officer or an officer designated by the Central Government in this behalf may, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the licensee or agent of such vessel, by order in writing and for reasons to be recorded therein, detain that vessel until an order is issued for the release of such vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (105893)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `National Coastal and Inland Shipping Strategic Plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105893&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, within`
  line `a period of two years from the date of commencement of this Act, by notification, publish a National Coastal`
  line `and Inland Shipping Strategic Plan for the purposes of this Act, which shall be updated every two years by`
  line `a like notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Strategic Plan shall include the following, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) assessment of the condition of coastal shipping routes in India including routes occupied by inland`
  line waterways;
  line
  line `(b) identification of the operational improvements required in coastal shipping, including those by`
  line `way of integration with inland waterway routes, in order to make coastal maritime transport a`
  line `cost-efficient mode of transportation for goods and passengers;`
  line
  line `(c) long term forecasts of traffic on coastal shipping and inland waterways network;`
  line
  line `(d) identification of best practices for improving the performance of coastal shipping including the`
  line `synergy presented by inland waterway routes and other modes of transportation;`
  line
  line `(e) identification of new routes for coastal shipping and integration thereof with inland waterways`
  line `and existing coastal shipping routes;`
  line
  line `(f) measures for the promotion of building, registration and participation of Indian vessels in coastal`
  line `shipping in India;`
  line
  line `(g) recommendations regarding the conditions subject to which vessels registered under the Inland`
  line `Vessels Act, 2021 (24 of 2021), may engage in coasting trade of India; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall constitute a committee consisting of the following members for`
  line `preparing the Strategic Plan, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) Director-General of Shipping---Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Chairman, Inland Waterways Authority of India constituted under section 3 of the Inland`
  line `Waterways Authority of India Act, 1985 (82 of 1985)---Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) one representative of each Board of Major Port Authority constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3 of the Major Port Authority Act, 2021 (1 of 2021)---Members;`
  line
  line `(d) one representative of the National Security Council Secretariat---Member;`
  line
  line `(e) one representative of each State Maritime Board or any other body responsible for the`
  line `administration of ports other than major ports, in a State or Union territory---Members;`
  line
  line `(f) two representatives to represent ship owners---Members;`
  line
  line `(g) two representatives of seafarers---Members; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other persons having expertise in the field of coastal trade, mercantile and marine trade or`
  line `maritime sector, as the Central Government may deem necessary---Members.`
  line
  line `(4) The committee shall meet at such time and place, and shall observe such procedure for the transaction`
  line `of business at its meetings including the quorum at such meetings, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The committee shall prepare a draft of the Strategic Plan for consideration and approval of the Central`
  line `Government and the Central Government shall, after considering the draft Strategic Plan, approve the Plan`
  line `with or without modifications.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall make available the Strategic Plan on its website for public access.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (105894)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `National Database of Coastal Shipping.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105894&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director-General shall maintain a web portal of`
  line `a database to be called the National Database of Coastal Shipping in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The National Database of Coastal Shipping shall contain the following information on coasting trade`
  line `in India, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) applications received for licence under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) licences granted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) terms and conditions of the licences so granted;`
  line
  line `(d) routes, voyages and services in the coasting trade of India;`
  line
  line `(e) requirement of applicants for grant of licences under section 4;`
  line
  line `(f) expired and revoked licences under section 5;`
  line
  line `(g) information reported to the Director-General under section 6;`
  line
  line `(h) such other information as the Director-General may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director-General shall make available the National Database of Coastal Shipping in electronic`
  line `form on a web portal for access to the public and it shall be updated every month.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (105895)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Application of Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105895&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `This Chapter shall apply to all sea going vessels chartered by a citizen`
  line `of India or a non-resident Indian or an overseas citizen of India, or a company or a co-operative society or`
  line `a limited liability partnership or any other entity as the Central Government may, by notification, specify`
  line `in this behalf, proceeding to sea from a port or place---`
  line
  line `(a) in India, to a port or place outside India; or`
  line
  line `(b) outside India, to a port or place in India or outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (105896)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Requirement of licence by chartered vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105896&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) No vessel, other than an Indian vessel,`
  line `chartered by a citizen of India or a non-resident Indian or an overseas citizen of India or a company or a`
  line `co-operative society or a limited liability partnership or any other entity as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification specify in this behalf, shall be taken to sea from a port or place within India or outside India,`
  line `except under a licence granted by the Director-General under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that no vessel which is chartered by an overseas citizen of India shall be required to obtain`
  line `licence, if such vessel is chartered exclusively for operation outside India.`
  line
  line `(2) A licence granted under this section may be---`
  line
  line `(a) a general licence; or`
  line
  line `(b) a licence for a specified period or voyage.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for the grant of a licence under this section shall be made to the Director-General`
  line `in such form, manner and on payment of such fee, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) A licence granted under this section shall be in such form, for such period and shall be subject to`
  line `such conditions, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director-General may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, specify such other`
  line `conditions as may be necessary, for grant of the licence under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (105897)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Suspension, revocation or modification of licence granted to chartered vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105897&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Director-General may, at any time, if the circumstances of the case so require, by order in writing and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded therein, suspend, revoke or modify a licence granted under section 11:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such licence shall be suspended, revoked or modified, unless the licensee has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) A licensee, who intends to modify the particulars of the licence granted to him under section 11, may`
  line `make an application to the Director-General in that behalf in such form and manner, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (105898)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Licence granted to chartered vessel to be returned when ceases to be valid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105898&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where a licence`
  line `granted under section 11 ceases to be valid due to expiry of its period or revocation, the licensee shall return`
  line `it or cause it to be returned to the Director-General, within such period as may be specified by the`
  line Director-General.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (105899)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `No port clearance without production of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105899&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No proper officer shall grant port clearance to`
  line `any vessel requiring a licence under this Chapter, unless the owner, master or agent of the vessel produces`
  line `a valid licence in respect of such vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (105900)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Punishment for participating in coasting trade in contravention of section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105900&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Whoever engages`
  line `in coasting trade in contravention of the provisions of section 3, shall be punishable with imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees, or four times`
  line `the value of all fees or commission or payments received by the owner or charterer of the vessel for the`
  line `voyage, whichever is greater, or with both, and the vessel shall also be liable for detention under`
  line `section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (105901)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Punishment for participating in coasting trade after licence ceases to be valid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105901&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `engages in coasting trade in contravention of the provisions of clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 5,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten lakh rupees, or two times the value of all fees or commission or payments received by the`
  line `licensee of the vessel for all voyages conducted in contravention, whichever is greater, or with both, and`
  line `the vessel shall also be liable for detention under section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (105902)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Punishment for taking vessel to sea in contravention of section 11.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105902&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Whoever takes a vessel to`
  line `sea in contravention of the provisions of section 11, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees, or four times the value of`
  line `all fees or commission or payments received by the owner or charterer of the vessel for the voyage,`
  line `whichever is greater, or with both, and the vessel shall also be liable for detention under section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (105903)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Punishment for failure to furnish information or furnishing false information after notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105903&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If any licensee or agent on whom a notice has been served under sub-section (2) of section 35---`
  line
  line `(a) fails to furnish the information required within the time specified; or`
  line
  line `(b) furnishes any information or makes any statement which the licensee or agent knows to be false`
  line `on any material particular,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or with both, and the vessel shall also be liable for detention under`
  line `section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (105904)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Punishment for violation of order of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105904&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If any vessel in respect of which a notice or`
  line `order for detention has been served under this Act, proceeds to sea before it is released, the licensee of the`
  line `vessel in respect of which the contravention has taken place shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees, or with both,`
  line `and the vessel shall also be liable for detention under section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (105905)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Punishment for illegally detaining person authorised to detain vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105905&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where any vessel, after`
  line `detention or order for such detention proceeds to sea with any person authorised to detain any vessel on`
  line `board before it is released, the licensee or agent of such vessel shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months or with fine upto one lakh rupees and all expenses of, and incidental`
  line `to, such person being so taken to sea, or with both, and the vessel shall also be liable for detention under`
  line `section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (105906)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Penalty for reporting false or misleading information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105906&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If any person who is required to report`
  line `any information to the Director-General under section 6 fails to do so, or otherwise intentionally reports`
  line `misleading or false information, such person shall be liable for penalty which may extend to one lakh`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (105907)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Penalty for violation of conditions of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105907&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails to comply with the conditions of`
  line `licence granted under section 4 or section 11, shall be liable for penalty which may extend to ten lakh`
  line `rupees, or two times the value of all fees or commission or payments received by the licensee of the vessel`
  line `for all voyages conducted in contravention, whichever is greater, or with both, and the vessel shall also be`
  line `liable for detention under section 29`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (105908)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Penalty for non-compliance of direction of Director-General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105908&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any licensee or agent, who fails`
  line `to comply with any direction of the Director-General under sub-section (1) of section 35, shall be liable for`
  line `penalty which may extend to five lakh rupees, or two times the value of all fees or commission or payments`
  line `received by such licensee or agent for all voyages conducted in contravention of such direction, whichever`
  line `is greater, and the vessel shall also be liable for detention under section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (105909)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Penalty for non-compliance with order of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105909&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Any licensee or agent, who`
  line `fails to comply with an order of the Central Government under this Act, shall be liable for penalty of not`
  line `less than fifteen lakh rupees, and the vessel may also be liable for detention under section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (105910)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `General provision for contravention or non-compliance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105910&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision`
  line `of this Act, or fails to comply with any provision thereof, or of any rule, direction, order or notification`
  line `made thereunder, for which no punishment or penalty is specially provided in this Act, shall be liable for`
  line `penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees, and if the breach is a continuing one, with further penalty`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees for every day after the first day during which the breach`
  line continues.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (105911)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Compounding of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105911&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Bharatiya`
  line `Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 (46 of 2023), any offence punishable under sections 15 to 20 of this Act`
  line `may, before or after the institution of prosecution, be compounded by an officer designated by the Central`
  line `Government by notification in this behalf, on payment for credit to the Central Government of such sum`
  line `and in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sum shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine which may be`
  line `imposed under this Act for the offences so compounded:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of subsequent offence, the same shall not be compounded.`
  line
  line `(2) The officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall exercise the powers to compound an offence, subject`
  line `to the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for the compounding of an offence shall be made in such form and manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall be`
  line `instituted against the offender in relation to whom the offence is so compounded.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the compounding of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such`
  line `composition shall be brought by the officer referred to in sub-section (1), in writing, to the notice of the`
  line `court in which the prosecution is pending and on such notice for compounding the offence being given, the`
  line `person against whom the offence is so compounded shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person who fails to comply with an order of compounding made by the officer referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), shall be liable to pay a sum equivalent to twenty per cent. of the maximum fine provided`
  line `for the offence, in addition to fine provided for the said offence.`
  line
  line `(7) No offence punishable under this Act shall be compounded except in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (105912)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Special provision regarding punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105912&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 23 of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 (46 of 2023), it shall be lawful for a Judicial Magistrate of`
  line `the first class to pass any sentence provided under this Act on any person convicted of an offence under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (105913)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105913&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company,`
  line `every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in-charge of, and was responsible to, the`
  line `company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in this Act, if such person proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that`
  line `such person exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that such offence was committed with the consent or connivance`
  line `of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or partner, or other officer`
  line `of the company, such director, manager, secretary or partner, or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall also be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "company" includes a co-operative society, a firm or limited liability partnership firm or other`
  line `association of individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (105914)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to enforce detention of vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105914&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Where a vessel is authorised or ordered to be detained under`
  line `this Act, any commissioned officer of the Indian Navy or Indian Coast Guard, or Police, or any port officer,`
  line `pilot, harbour master or conservator of port, or the Commissioner of Customs, or any other person`
  line `authorised under this Act, may detain the vessel under instructions of the principal officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (105915)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Adjudicating officer for imposition of penalty, appeal and procedure therefor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105915&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `principal officer shall be the adjudicating officer for the purposes of imposing penalty under sections 21`
  line `to 25.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by the order of the principal officer imposing the penalty under`
  line `sub-section (1) may, within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of such order, prefer an appeal`
  line `before the Director-General in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director-General shall dispose of an appeal referred to in sub-section (2) within a period of thirty`
  line `days from the date of receipt of such appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) No order shall be passed under this section unless the parties have been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) Any penalty imposed under sections 21 to 25 may be compounded for the first contravention by an`
  line `officer designated by the Central Government by notification in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if a penalty imposed by the principal officer or the`
  line `Director-General under this Chapter is not deposited, the amount shall be recovered as an arrear of land`
  line revenue.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (105916)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Notice in respect of foreign vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105916&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `If any vessel, other than an Indian vessel, is detained under`
  line `this Act, or if any proceeding is taken under this Act against the licensee or agent of such vessel, notice`
  line `shall forthwith be served on the consular office of the country in which such vessel is registered, or nearest`
  line `to the port where the vessel is for the time being, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, and such`
  line `notice shall specify the grounds on which the vessel has been detained or the proceedings have been taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (105917)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Place of trial and jurisdiction of court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105917&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Any person who commits an offence under this Act or`
  line `any rules made thereunder, may be tried for such offence in any place in which such person may be found,`
  line `or in any court which the Central Government may, by notification, direct in this behalf, or in any court in`
  line `which such person might be tried under any other law for time being in force in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (105918)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Service of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105918&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Where, for the purposes of this Act, any document is to be served on any`
  line `person, that document may be served,---`
  line
  line `(a) in any case by delivering a copy thereof personally to the person to be served, or by leaving the`
  line `same at his last place of residence, or by post or by such electronic means as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) on the master of a vessel where there is master, or on the person being or appearing to be in`
  line `command or charge of the vessel, by leaving the same for him on board that vessel; and`
  line
  line `(c) on the owner of the vessel where there is no master and the vessel is in India, or if such owner is`
  line `not in India, on the agent of the owner residing in India, or, where no such agent is known or is found,`
  line `by affixing at a suitable place on the bridge of the vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (105919)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105919&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by general or special order, direct that any`
  line `power, authority or jurisdiction exercisable by it under or in relation to any of the provisions of this Act,`
  line `may be exercisable also by the Director-General or such other officer and subject to such conditions as may`
  line `be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director-General may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, by general or`
  line `special order, direct that any power or authority conferred upon or delegated to, and any duty imposed upon`
  line `him by or under this Act, may be exercised or discharged also by such officer or authority and subject to`
  line `such conditions as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (105920)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Director-General to give directions and seek information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105920&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director-General`
  line may,---
  line
  line `(a) in the public interest; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the interest of Indian shipping; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the interest of national defence and maritime security; or`
  line
  line `(d) for ensuring safety of life at sea and the safety of environment,`
  line
  line `by order, direct any vessel for which licence has been granted under this Act, in respect of the following,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the ports or places, whether within or outside India, to which, and the routes by which, the vessel`
  line `shall proceed for any particular purpose;`
  line
  line `(ii) the diversion of a vessel from one route to another for any particular purpose;`
  line
  line `(iii) the classes of passengers or cargo which may be carried in the vessel;`
  line
  line `(iv) the order of priority in which passengers or cargo may be taken on or put off the vessel at any`
  line `port or place, whether within or outside India;`
  line
  line `(v) to ban any vessel from entering any port, anchorage or offshore facility in India;`
  line
  line `(vi) any other matter which the Director-General may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director-General may, by notice, require the licensee or agent of any vessel in respect of`
  line which---
  line
  line `(a) licence is granted under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) any direction is given relating to diversion of a vessel from one route to another for any particular`
  line purpose,
  line
  line `to furnish such information as may be considered necessary within such period as may be specified in the`
  line `said notice, which may include---`
  line
  line `(i) the classes of passengers and cargo which the ship is about to carry, or is capable of carrying, or`
  line `has carried during any specified period; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the rates of passenger fares and freight charges applicable to the vessel; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other matter as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (105921)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105921&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, every person shall, in the discharge of his functions and duties under this Act, be bound by such`
  line `directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give to it in writing from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government as to whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (105922)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105922&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any law for the time being`
  line `in force, the Central Government or, as the case may be, the Director-General with the prior permission of`
  line `the Central Government, if is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest so to do, may,`
  line `by order in writing and subject to such conditions and for such period as it may think fit, exempt from the`
  line `provisions of this Act,---`
  line
  line `(a) any vessel or class of vessels engaged in coasting trade; or`
  line
  line `(b) any class of vessels chartered by a citizen of India or non-resident Indian or an overseas citizen`
  line `of India, or a company or a co-operative society or a limited liability partnership or such entities as may`
  line `be specified by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (105923)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105923&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (105924)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105924&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, subject to the`
  line `condition of previous publication, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner of application for grant of licence and the fee to be paid for the same under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the form, period and the conditions subject to which licence shall be granted under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the class or category of licence to be granted under sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and manner of making application for modification of particulars of a licence under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner of reporting the requirements to the Director-General under section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) such other matters to be included in the Strategic Plan under clause (h) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(g) the time, place and the procedure to be observed by the committee for the transaction of business`
  line `at its meetings and the quorum at such meetings under sub-section (4) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(h) the form and manner of maintaining the National Database of Coastal Shipping by the`
  line `Director-General under sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner of application for grant of licence and the fee to be paid under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) the form, period and the conditions subject to which licence shall be granted under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 11;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and manner of making application for modification of particulars of a licence under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(l) the sum to be paid for credit to the Central Government for compounding an offence and the`
  line `manner of making the payment under sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and manner of making an application for the compounding of an offence under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(n) the form and manner of preferring appeal to the Director-General under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner of issuance of notice under section 31;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matters in respect of which the Director-General may, by notice, require the licensee or`
  line `agent of any vessel to furnish information under sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(q) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed for carrying out the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (105925)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Laying of rules and notifications before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105925&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made and every notification`
  line `issued under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `notification or both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made or issued, the rule or`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (105926)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105926&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the date`
  line `of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (105927)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360&sectionId=105927&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00007_2025-20_1777265394360
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Part XIV of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958) (herein`
  line `referred to as Part XIV of the said Act), except section 411A thereof, is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,---`
  line
  line `(a) any rule, regulation, bye-law, order, notification or exemption made, issued or granted under Part`
  line `XIV of the said Act shall, until revoked, have effect as if it had been made, issued or granted under the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any licence granted or issued under Part XIV of the said Act shall, until it is revoked or expires,`
  line `have effect as if it had been issued or granted under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any office established or created, officer or person appointed and any body elected or constituted`
  line `under Part XIV of the said Act shall continue and shall be deemed to have been established, created,`
  line `appointed, elected, or constituted, as the case may be, under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) any document referring to Part XIV of the said Act shall be construed as referring to this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) any fine levied under Part XIV of the said Act may be recovered as if it had been levied under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) any offence committed under Part XIV of the said Act may be prosecuted and punished as if it`
  line `had been committed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) any proceeding pending before any court under Part XIV of the said Act may be tried or disposed`
  line `of under the corresponding provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) any inspection, investigation or inquiry ordered to be done under the provisions of Part XIV of`
  line `the said Act shall continue to be proceeded with as if such inspection, investigation or inquiry is ordered`
  line `to be done under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), the provisions of section 6 of the General`
  line `Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply with regard to the effect of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
